<br />
<br />I'm just speaking because I've been badly burned from qbasic.  One time, I misused poke and overwrote my program in memory, another time I hit the maximum code size wall, and couldn't add any more code, or even run or save the file.  Even though I'm a former qbasic fanatic, the Zelda 2 editor was way too much for it to handle.

		

